President Trump and President Moon of South Korea held discussions on trade and North Korea during their meeting at the United Nations Headquarters. They announced the signing of an important trade agreement between the two countries, which they believe will be beneficial for both South Korea and the United States. They also expressed satisfaction with the progress being made in regards to North Korea's denuclearization. President Moon conveyed a message from Chairman Kim expressing his commitment to denuclearization and his hope to meet with President Trump soon. President Trump mentioned that a second summit with Chairman Kim is being planned and that progress is being made in the relationship with North Korea. He also mentioned the upcoming meeting with Rod Rosenstein, stating that he wants transparency and openness. President Trump highlighted the strong performance of the US economy, with record employment numbers and low unemployment rates for various demographics. He also mentioned the return of companies to the US and the country's status as the fastest growing economy in the world.